WEBVTT

00:00:55.399 --> 00:00:56.320
What is going on?

00:00:56.320 --> 00:00:57.159
I don't know.

00:00:59.840 --> 00:01:01.280
Teach me a lesson?

00:01:01.759 --> 00:01:03.359
Is this the lesson you're teaching me?

00:01:06.519 --> 00:01:07.760
Maybe he wants to tell you

00:01:07.840 --> 00:01:09.239
the wrong way to play.

00:01:09.920 --> 00:01:10.719
Originally, I just wanted

00:01:10.719 --> 00:01:12.359
to hold a Five Dragons Challenge

00:01:12.359 --> 00:01:13.439
to generate some buzz.

00:01:13.719 --> 00:01:15.480
But I didn't expect your sudden appearance

00:01:15.840 --> 00:01:17.640
to actually increase the attention.

00:01:17.920 --> 00:01:19.799
Especially after your big talk just now

00:01:21.120 --> 00:01:22.719
about challenging the Five Dragons.

00:01:23.159 --> 00:01:23.840
In the first game,

00:01:24.280 --> 00:01:25.640
you lost so miserably.

00:01:26.359 --> 00:01:27.760
But I really have to thank you.

00:01:29.760 --> 00:01:30.319
Thank you

00:01:30.920 --> 00:01:32.120
for making me even more money.

00:01:37.079 --> 00:01:37.879
Your turn.

00:01:38.879 --> 00:01:39.680
At a time like this,

00:01:39.799 --> 00:01:40.480
you're still pretending?

00:01:41.680 --> 00:01:43.519
You won't turn back until you hit a wall.

00:01:43.760 --> 00:01:45.640
The reason you won before

00:01:47.640 --> 00:01:48.959
was all due to luck.

00:01:50.159 --> 00:01:51.560
It won't be so easy this time.

00:01:51.760 --> 00:01:52.439
Boss Nan.

00:01:52.799 --> 00:01:53.480
Forget it.

00:01:53.879 --> 00:01:55.560
This kid is crazy.

00:01:56.599 --> 00:01:57.359
Just try and shoot.

00:01:58.439 --> 00:01:59.280
Fine.

00:01:59.760 --> 00:02:01.879
I'll show you exactly how you lose.

00:02:15.800 --> 00:02:16.599
Shoot!

00:02:33.120 --> 00:02:34.000
What is going on?

00:02:34.199 --> 00:02:36.439
Is this a contest to see who makes more mistakes?

00:02:37.719 --> 00:02:38.159
Boss Nan.

00:02:38.879 --> 00:02:39.840
I don't know.

00:02:51.360 --> 00:02:53.080
What kind of tricks did you use?

00:02:53.280 --> 00:02:54.159
No tricks.

00:02:55.080 --> 00:02:56.439
Just psychological warfare.

00:02:57.280 --> 00:02:59.439
Tiangong Style: The Nine Purple Mind-Flame.

00:02:59.719 --> 00:03:02.039
The only mind-attack technique in the Tiangong Style.

00:03:02.520 --> 00:03:04.039
After discovering the opponent's weakness,

00:03:04.280 --> 00:03:06.400
it helps the opponent constantly magnify their own flaws.

00:03:07.120 --> 00:03:09.400
Like planting a flame in the opponent's heart,

00:03:09.560 --> 00:03:10.919
causing them to destroy themselves.

00:03:11.639 --> 00:03:12.599
Psychological warfare?

00:03:13.680 --> 00:03:15.080
Psychological warfare...

00:03:16.319 --> 00:03:17.759
You're not trying to tell me

00:03:17.919 --> 00:03:20.120
you can make me lose just by talking trash?

00:03:20.360 --> 00:03:21.759
It's not me making you lose.

00:03:22.479 --> 00:03:23.520
It's yourself.

00:03:23.919 --> 00:03:25.919
You try so hard to hit a more powerful power shot,

00:03:26.360 --> 00:03:28.360
but it only magnifies your fatal flaw.

00:03:33.759 --> 00:03:35.520
You must sink this ball for me!

00:03:36.120 --> 00:03:37.360
Or you know the consequences.

00:03:40.280 --> 00:03:41.039
Coincidence.

00:03:41.719 --> 00:03:42.840
It's all a coincidence.

00:03:43.639 --> 00:03:44.599
Such a simple shot,

00:03:44.759 --> 00:03:46.080
there's no way I can't make it.

00:04:19.120 --> 00:04:19.839
This is...

00:04:20.480 --> 00:04:21.720
According to Center-Table rules,

00:04:21.959 --> 00:04:24.120
you knocked both the white and black balls off the table.

00:04:24.680 --> 00:04:25.519
You are out.

00:04:25.800 --> 00:04:26.480
Why?

00:04:26.800 --> 00:04:28.560
Tell me why this is happening!

00:04:34.639 --> 00:04:35.959
A scratched white ball

00:04:35.959 --> 00:04:38.040
does indeed affect a top player's feel.

00:04:38.519 --> 00:04:39.560
But the faster the ball speed,

00:04:40.240 --> 00:04:41.560
the greater the effect on the ball.

00:04:42.079 --> 00:04:43.160
So your tricks

00:04:43.360 --> 00:04:46.079
actually affect you, who loves power shots.

00:04:46.800 --> 00:04:49.240
Especially since you used a specially treated cue stick.

00:05:06.560 --> 00:05:07.160
Boss Nan!

00:05:07.680 --> 00:05:08.000
Boss Nan!

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:08.319
It's nothing.

00:05:12.439 --> 00:05:13.399
Boss Nan, don't!

00:05:14.000 --> 00:05:14.959
Don't, Boss Nan!

00:05:15.319 --> 00:05:16.000
Boss Nan!

00:05:16.759 --> 00:05:17.680
Boss Nan!

00:05:24.920 --> 00:05:26.439
It's not over yet.

00:05:43.240 --> 00:05:45.040
I'm not like Iron Arm Hong,

00:05:45.319 --> 00:05:46.480
all muscle,

00:05:46.560 --> 00:05:48.600
an idiot who only plays violent Center-Table.

00:05:49.560 --> 00:05:51.120
Nine-ball requires aesthetics.

00:05:51.519 --> 00:05:52.279
Don't you think?

00:05:52.519 --> 00:05:53.079
Hei Ba.

00:06:08.279 --> 00:06:10.040
I can't blame you for missing.

00:06:10.319 --> 00:06:10.959
After all,

00:06:11.120 --> 00:06:12.439
a rail ball requiring a bank shot

00:06:12.720 --> 00:06:13.959
is indeed hard to play.

00:06:23.199 --> 00:06:25.680
Always setting you up with such difficult shots,

00:06:26.000 --> 00:06:27.800
I'm almost feeling a bit embarrassed.

00:06:29.079 --> 00:06:29.959
You've improved a lot.

00:06:31.680 --> 00:06:33.279
A man who loves to lecture.

00:06:33.279 --> 00:06:34.439
You're really patronizing.

00:06:35.240 --> 00:06:36.000
Just shoot.

00:06:36.680 --> 00:06:38.120
Now that you've learned to use the rails,

00:06:38.399 --> 00:06:39.959
isn't defending much easier?

00:06:50.560 --> 00:06:52.199
Your spin shots are quite good.

00:06:52.759 --> 00:06:54.800
But you leave too much room for your opponent.

00:06:55.680 --> 00:06:56.879
Learn to use the rails a bit.

00:06:57.639 --> 00:06:58.759
Your defense will be better that way.

00:07:00.399 --> 00:07:01.879
It is very easy.

00:07:02.800 --> 00:07:03.839
I remember,

00:07:04.279 --> 00:07:05.639
you had a game back then

00:07:05.680 --> 00:07:07.399
where you relied solely on defense

00:07:07.399 --> 00:07:09.240
and secured the final victory.

00:07:10.079 --> 00:07:11.040
Who would have thought that today,

00:07:11.040 --> 00:07:11.839
this very tactic

00:07:12.199 --> 00:07:14.120
would be used against you?

00:07:14.800 --> 00:07:16.240
I'm not afraid to tell you,

00:07:16.720 --> 00:07:18.120
every shot I take from now on

00:07:18.279 --> 00:07:19.439
will be played this way.

00:07:19.800 --> 00:07:20.759
Let's see how you win.

00:07:21.319 --> 00:07:22.360
Compared to Center-Table,

00:07:22.839 --> 00:07:24.680
9-ball indeed relies more on defense.

00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:25.680
I have to admit,

00:07:26.920 --> 00:07:28.240
your defense is really quite good.

00:07:28.639 --> 00:07:30.600
If you admit defeat now,

00:07:30.800 --> 00:07:32.319
maybe if I'm in a good mood,

00:07:32.920 --> 00:07:34.120
I might even teach you.

00:07:36.399 --> 00:07:37.199
But you forgot

00:07:37.199 --> 00:07:39.079
the most important thing in billiards.

00:07:39.279 --> 00:07:41.199
Seven-Star Chain.

00:07:41.439 --> 00:07:43.759
Using defensive spin shots for offense.

00:07:43.800 --> 00:07:44.759
As long as you keep potting balls,

00:07:45.240 --> 00:07:46.879
you won't give your opponent a chance to defend.

00:07:46.879 --> 00:07:47.680
Whether it's 9-ball

00:07:48.480 --> 00:07:49.279
or Snooker,

00:07:50.079 --> 00:07:50.519
defense

00:07:50.680 --> 00:07:51.759
is always a crucial part.

00:07:52.199 --> 00:07:53.680
But if you want to win...

00:07:54.399 --> 00:07:55.600
You still think you can win?

00:08:05.319 --> 00:08:05.959
Yeah!

00:08:07.040 --> 00:08:08.360
Although defense is important,

00:08:08.879 --> 00:08:09.879
the fun of the game

00:08:09.879 --> 00:08:11.360
lies in potting the balls.

00:08:12.199 --> 00:08:12.800
Doesn't it?

00:08:13.879 --> 00:08:15.120
Especially in 9-ball,

00:08:15.600 --> 00:08:17.240
where whoever pots the 9-ball first

00:08:17.560 --> 00:08:18.639
wins the match.

00:08:21.519 --> 00:08:23.120
Hei Ba won two games in a row so quickly.

00:08:23.279 --> 00:08:24.279
Let me check the odds.

00:08:24.480 --> 00:08:25.639
I should have bet more on Hei Ba.

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:26.959
How is the betting pool looking now?

00:08:28.560 --> 00:08:29.600
People betting on Hei Ba to win

00:08:29.639 --> 00:08:30.399
are increasing.

00:08:30.680 --> 00:08:31.199
Close the betting pool.

00:08:31.639 --> 00:08:32.240
Now!

00:08:32.320 --> 00:08:32.919
Captain Jack.

00:08:33.399 --> 00:08:34.000
It's Captain Jack.

00:08:35.159 --> 00:08:35.879
What did you say?

00:08:38.000 --> 00:08:38.600
I've said it before.

00:08:38.840 --> 00:08:39.440
Everyone

00:08:39.559 --> 00:08:40.960
has their own inherent habits.

00:08:41.039 --> 00:08:41.799
Their playing style,

00:08:42.200 --> 00:08:42.879
even their tone of voice,

00:08:42.919 --> 00:08:43.200
movements,

00:08:43.480 --> 00:08:44.200
and walking posture.

00:08:44.360 --> 00:08:45.320
These things can't lie.

00:08:45.840 --> 00:08:46.240
Therefore,

00:08:46.399 --> 00:08:47.720
he must be Captain Jack.

00:08:48.200 --> 00:08:48.799
Impossible.

00:08:49.600 --> 00:08:50.960
After the Inescapable Net Tournament ended,

00:08:51.240 --> 00:08:52.879
Captain Jack vanished without a trace.

00:08:53.559 --> 00:08:55.360
Hasn't Hei Ba been delivering food all this time?

00:08:55.799 --> 00:08:57.240
How could he be Captain Jack?

00:08:57.600 --> 00:08:58.720
I lost to him before.

00:08:59.120 --> 00:09:00.399
So I know his playing style.

00:09:00.600 --> 00:09:01.399
But back then, I could only

00:09:01.399 --> 00:09:02.679
calculate 60% of his moves.

00:09:02.879 --> 00:09:03.360
But now,

00:09:04.240 --> 00:09:06.039
I'm confident I can calculate 90%.

00:09:06.919 --> 00:09:07.440
So,

00:09:08.720 --> 00:09:09.360
this time,

00:09:09.759 --> 00:09:10.639
I will definitely win.

00:09:13.960 --> 00:09:14.799
Then wait a bit longer.

00:09:15.240 --> 00:09:16.320
It's only been two games.

00:09:16.799 --> 00:09:18.240
Hei Ba can't keep winning forever.

00:09:19.159 --> 00:09:20.960
And he absolutely cannot be Captain Jack.

00:09:29.600 --> 00:09:30.440
I recognize you.

00:09:31.039 --> 00:09:32.000
You are Captain Jack.

00:09:32.200 --> 00:09:32.799
Aren't you?

00:09:42.120 --> 00:09:42.919
Nice!

00:09:43.840 --> 00:09:44.720
So cool!

00:09:44.720 --> 00:09:45.600
Miracle Hei Ba!

00:09:47.320 --> 00:09:47.840
Yeah!

00:09:48.840 --> 00:09:55.159
Champion! Champion! Champion!